    public class Game
extends javax.swing.JFrame
implements java.awt.event.KeyListener, java.awt.event.ActionListener
    The main driver class of the program. This class stores the frames for the GUI, and listens for user keyboard input to create responses in the GUI.

        public void startGame​(int numOrders,
                      boolean isNetworking)
        Starts up a game with a specified number of derivative orders, and either networking or no networking.
        Parameters:
        numOrders - number of derivatives to find in this game
        isNetworking - this specific game is multiplayer if isNetworking is true, and single-player if it's false.
